---
import { C, FONT } from "../infographicTokens";
---

<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 720 320" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
  <title>What makes up a cooling load: sensible plus latent</title>
  <desc>
    A cooling load is the sum of sensible heat (conduction through the shell, solar gain through glass,
    and internal gains from people and appliances) and latent heat (the energy to remove moisture).
    A heating load uses the sensible conduction and infiltration side only.
  </desc>

  <rect x="8" y="8" width="704" height="304" rx="12" fill={C.panelBg} stroke={C.border} />
  <text x="24" y="36" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="14" font-weight="700">Cooling load = sensible + latent</text>
  <text x="24" y="56" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="11">Heat you feel (temperature) plus the energy to dry out humid air</text>

  <!-- Sensible block -->
  <rect x="24" y="80" width="420" height="120" rx="10" fill={C.blueLight} stroke={C.blue} stroke-width="1.5" />
  <text x="40" y="104" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="13" font-weight="700">Sensible heat</text>
  <text x="40" y="122" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="10">Raises air temperature — the bulk of most loads</text>
  <rect x="40" y="136" width="124" height="48" rx="7" fill={C.white} stroke={C.blue} stroke-width="1.1" />
  <text x="102" y="156" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5" font-weight="700">Conduction</text>
  <text x="102" y="172" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="9.5">walls, roof, floor</text>
  <rect x="174" y="136" width="124" height="48" rx="7" fill={C.white} stroke={C.blue} stroke-width="1.1" />
  <text x="236" y="156" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5" font-weight="700">Solar gain</text>
  <text x="236" y="172" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="9.5">through windows</text>
  <rect x="308" y="136" width="124" height="48" rx="7" fill={C.white} stroke={C.blue} stroke-width="1.1" />
  <text x="370" y="156" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5" font-weight="700">Internal</text>
  <text x="370" y="172" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="9.5">people, lights</text>

  <!-- Latent block -->
  <rect x="460" y="80" width="236" height="120" rx="10" fill={C.primaryLight} stroke={C.primary} stroke-width="1.5" />
  <text x="476" y="104" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="13" font-weight="700">Latent heat</text>
  <text x="476" y="122" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="10">Removes moisture, not temperature</text>
  <rect x="476" y="136" width="204" height="48" rx="7" fill={C.white} stroke={C.primary} stroke-width="1.1" />
  <text x="578" y="156" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5" font-weight="700">Humidity load</text>
  <text x="578" y="172" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="9.5">outdoor air, cooking, showers</text>

  <!-- Heating note -->
  <rect x="24" y="216" width="672" height="80" rx="10" fill={C.orangeLight} stroke={C.orange} stroke-width="1.5" />
  <text x="40" y="240" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="12" font-weight="700">A heating load is simpler</text>
  <text x="40" y="260" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5">It is a heat-loss number — sensible conduction plus infiltration, driven by ΔT.</text>
  <text x="40" y="278" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5">No solar gain, no latent moisture. That is why summer and winter loads rarely match.</text>
</svg>
